A Nigerian citizen, Charles Diffodile, has been arrested by the police for trafficking banned drugs from Kerala to Bengaluru, India. According to the Times of India, 55 grams of Methylenedioxymethamphetamine were seized from Diffodile at the time of his arrest. ALSO READ: Collapsing 2-storey building kills 3 in Rivers communnity “He was distributing narcotics to many areas inside Kerala. Police were investigating a drug case which led to the arrest of Charles from Bengaluru, Karnataka. He was on bail after another narcotic case,” the police said. 